title: The tyde taryeth no man A moste pleasant and merry commody, right pythie and full of delight. Compiled by George Wapull. Fovvre persons may easily play it. ...
author: Wapull, George, fl. 1576.
publisher: In Fleetestreate, beneath the Conduite, at the signe of Saynt Iohn Euaungelist, by Hugh Iackson,
notes: Running title reads: A new commody called The tyde taryeth no man.
